-- U.S. Bancorp Promotes Elmore, Stone, Chosy in Management Shuffle
-- B y   L a u r a   M a r c i n e k
-- 2012-12-11T18:52:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-11/u-s-bancorp-promotes-elmore-stone-chosy-in-management-shuffle.html
U.S. Bancorp named three executives
to new posts, with John Elmore and Kent Stone replacing Richard
Hartnack as vice chairman of consumer and small business
banking, and James Chosy taking over from Lee Mitau as executive
vice president and general counsel.  The three will join the 15-member managing committee and
report to Chief Executive Officer  Richard Davis , the
Minneapolis-based lender said today in a statement. The changes
are effective March 1, the bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laura Marcinek in  New York  at 
